'''Furshlugginer''' is one of several words made up by the original writers of [[Mad (magazine)|MAD Magazine]], "Furshlugginer" is an adjective with as many possible meanings as the user deems necessary. Often used in a negative sense (ex: "You Furshlugginer robot! Can't you do anything right?"), it came into almost-popular usage in the late Seventies and early Eighties by those seeking a more gonzo state of conciousness.

The word may have Germanic or Yiddish connotations. It is roughly homophonous to the German adjective "verschlagen", meaning devious, shifty or whily. The prefix "ver-", or "far-" in Yiddish, is a negative modifier to the word it preceedes.

